children.text: The charged rainwater system does not have the strainer and rain-head installed at the top of the downpipe to ensure that the system remains clean.

The relevant Australian Standard, AS 3500.3 Plumbing and Drainage, Stormwater drainage requires that there be a minimum of 300mm of static head to ensure that the system operates properly. The Victorian Building Authority’s Technical Solution Sheet 0.01 states that
‘A rain-head and strainer is required at the eaves gutter connection to prevent debris entering and blocking the charged downpipe’.
